external_knowledge:
- "maritime giants" metaphorically refers to companies;
- "ocean of global business" refers to the Fortune 500 list;
- "weathered more than a decade" means the companies have been on the list for more than ten years;
- "keep their sail aloft" refers to maintaining a high level of profitability;
- "waters of industry" refers to the different sectors of business activity;
- "height of their sails" refers to the average profit levels.

sql:
SELECT companies.company_name, executives.executive_name 
FROM companies 
INNER JOIN executives ON companies.company_id = executives.company_id;
